events.description: A massive earthquake strikes Aleppo; it is one of the most destructive earthquakes ever.
events.html: • 1138 – A massive earthquake strikes Aleppo; it is one of the most destructive earthquakes ever.[1]

events.description: A peace treaty ends the Jin–Song wars.
events.html: • 1142 – A peace treaty ends the Jin–Song wars.

events.description: The peerage and clergy restrict the authority of English kings with the Ordinances of 1311.
events.html: • 1311 – The peerage and clergy restrict the authority of English kings with the Ordinances of 1311.

events.description: The New Netherland Company applies to the States General of the Netherlands for exclusive trading rights in what is now the northeastern United States.
events.html: • 1614 – The New Netherland Company applies to the States General of the Netherlands for exclusive trading rights in what is now the northeastern United States.

events.description: The Burchardi flood kills around 15,000 in North Friesland, Denmark and Germany.
events.html: • 1634 – The Burchardi flood kills around 15,000 in North Friesland, Denmark and Germany.

events.description: Cromwell's New Model Army sacks Wexford, killing over 2,000 Irish Confederate troops and 1,500 civilians.
events.html: • 1649 – Cromwell's New Model Army sacks Wexford, killing over 2,000 Irish Confederate troops and 1,500 civilians.

events.description: American Revolution: A fleet of American boats on Lake Champlain is defeated by the Royal Navy, but delays the British advance until 1777.
events.html: • 1776 – American Revolution: A fleet of American boats on Lake Champlain is defeated by the Royal Navy, but delays the British advance until 1777.

events.description: The Royal Navy decisively defeats the Batavian Navy at Camperdown during the French Revolutionary Wars.
events.html: • 1797 – The Royal Navy decisively defeats the Batavian Navy at Camperdown during the French Revolutionary Wars.

events.description: The Juliana begins operation as the first steam-powered ferry in New York harbor.
events.html: • 1811 – The Juliana begins operation as the first steam-powered ferry in New York harbor.

events.description: The Maronite leader Bashir Shihab II surrenders to the Ottoman Empire and later is sent to Malta in exile.
events.html: • 1840 – The Maronite leader Bashir Shihab II surrenders to the Ottoman Empire and later is sent to Malta in exile.

events.description: The University of Sydney, Australia's oldest university, is inaugurated in Sydney.
events.html: • 1852 – The University of Sydney, Australia's oldest university, is inaugurated in Sydney.

events.description: American Civil War: Confederate troops conduct a raid on Chambersburg, Pennsylvania.
events.html: • 1862 – American Civil War: Confederate troops conduct a raid on Chambersburg, Pennsylvania.

events.description: Hundreds of black men and women march in Jamaica, starting the Morant Bay rebellion.
events.html: • 1865 – Hundreds of black men and women march in Jamaica, starting the Morant Bay rebellion.

events.description: In Washington, D.C., the Daughters of the American Revolution is founded.
events.html: • 1890 – In Washington, D.C., the Daughters of the American Revolution is founded.

events.description: The Second Boer War erupts in South Africa between the British-ruled Cape Colony, and the Boer-ruled Transvaal and Orange Free State.
events.html: • 1899 – The Second Boer War erupts in South Africa between the British-ruled Cape Colony, and the Boer-ruled Transvaal and Orange Free State.

events.description: San Francisco sparks a diplomatic crisis between the United States and Japan by ordering segregated schools for Japanese students.
events.html: • 1906 – San Francisco sparks a diplomatic crisis between the United States and Japan by ordering segregated schools for Japanese students.

events.description: Piloted by Arch Hoxsey, Theodore Roosevelt becomes the first U.S. president to fly in an airplane.
events.html: • 1910 – Piloted by Arch Hoxsey, Theodore Roosevelt becomes the first U.S. president to fly in an airplane.

events.description: First Balkan War: The day after the Battle of Sarantaporo, Greek troops liberate the city of Kozani.
events.html: • 1912 – First Balkan War: The day after the Battle of Sarantaporo, Greek troops liberate the city of Kozani.

events.description: The 7.1 .mw-parser-output .tooltip-dotted{border-bottom:1px dotted;cursor:help}Mw San Fermín earthquake shakes Puerto Rico. The quake and resulting tsunami kill up to 116 people.
events.html: • 1918 – The 7.1 Mw San Fermín earthquake shakes Puerto Rico. The quake and resulting tsunami kill up to 116 people.

events.description: The Duke and Duchess of Windsor tour Nazi Germany for 12 days and meet Adolf Hitler on 22 October.
events.html: • 1937 – The Duke and Duchess of Windsor tour Nazi Germany for 12 days and meet Adolf Hitler on 22 October.

entities.name: Duke and Duchess of Windsor's tour of Germany, 1937

events.description: Beginning of the National Liberation War of Macedonia.
events.html: • 1941 – Beginning of the National Liberation War of Macedonia.

events.description: World War II: Off Guadalcanal, United States Navy ships intercept and defeat a Japanese force.
events.html: • 1942 – World War II: Off Guadalcanal, United States Navy ships intercept and defeat a Japanese force.

events.description: The Tuvan People's Republic is annexed by the Soviet Union.
events.html: • 1944 – The Tuvan People's Republic is annexed by the Soviet Union.

events.description: CBS's field-sequential color system for television is the first to be licensed for broadcast by the U.S. Federal Communications Commission.
events.html: • 1950 – CBS's field-sequential color system for television is the first to be licensed for broadcast by the U.S. Federal Communications Commission.

events.description: In accord with the 1954 Geneva Conference, French troops complete their withdrawal from North Vietnam.
events.html: • 1954 – In accord with the 1954 Geneva Conference, French troops complete their withdrawal from North Vietnam.

events.description: NASA launches Pioneer 1, its first space probe, although it fails to achieve a stable orbit.
events.html: • 1958 – NASA launches Pioneer 1, its first space probe, although it fails to achieve a stable orbit.

events.description: The Second Vatican Council becomes the first ecumenical council of the Roman Catholic Church in 92 years.
events.html: • 1962 – The Second Vatican Council becomes the first ecumenical council of the Roman Catholic Church in 92 years.

events.description: NASA launches Apollo 7, the first successful crewed Apollo mission.
events.html: • 1968 – NASA launches Apollo 7, the first successful crewed Apollo mission.

events.description: George Washington is posthumously promoted to the grade of General of the Armies.
events.html: • 1976 – George Washington is posthumously promoted to the grade of General of the Armies.

events.description: Aboard the Space Shuttle Challenger, astronaut Kathryn D. Sullivan becomes the first American woman to perform a space walk.
events.html: • 1984 – Aboard the Space Shuttle Challenger, astronaut Kathryn D. Sullivan becomes the first American woman to perform a space walk.

events.description: Aeroflot Flight 3352 crashes into maintenance vehicles upon landing in Omsk, Russia, killing 178.
events.html: • 1984 – Aeroflot Flight 3352 crashes into maintenance vehicles upon landing in Omsk, Russia, killing 178.

events.description: Ronald Reagan and Mikhail Gorbachev meet in Iceland to continue discussions about scaling back IRBM arsenals in Europe.
events.html: • 1986 – Ronald Reagan and Mikhail Gorbachev meet in Iceland to continue discussions about scaling back IRBM arsenals in Europe.

events.description: The AIDS Memorial Quilt is first displayed during the Second National March on Washington for Lesbian and Gay Rights.
events.html: • 1987 – The AIDS Memorial Quilt is first displayed during the Second National March on Washington for Lesbian and Gay Rights.

events.description: Start of Operation Pawan by Indian forces in Sri Lanka. Thousands of civilians, insurgents, soldiers die.
events.html: • 1987 – Start of Operation Pawan by Indian forces in Sri Lanka. Thousands of civilians, insurgents, soldiers die.

events.description: Prof. Anita Hill delivers her televised testimony concerning sexual harassment during the Clarence Thomas Supreme Court nomination.
events.html: • 1991 – Prof. Anita Hill delivers her televised testimony concerning sexual harassment during the Clarence Thomas Supreme Court nomination.[2]
